<td class="grey" align="center"><a name="3"></a><b>Design Notes</b></td>
</tr>
<tr valign="top">
<td>
<!--MAIN TABLES GO HERE-->
	<table border="0" cellpadding="10" cellspacing="0" width="100%">
	<tbody><tr valign="top">
	<td class="bodycopy">
		<!--BODYCOPY BEGINS HERE-->
<p>
Youngstown is named after the city in Ohio where the variant was created
and first played.  It is regarded by many as the oldest Diplomacy
variant.

<p>
The Youngstown variant played on the DPjudge is named
<a target=vb
href=http://www.variantbank.org/results/rules/y/youngstown.htm>Youngstown
IVa in the Variant Bank</a>.
This variant was created by Rod Walker, A. Phillips, Ken Lowe, and Jon Monsarret.

		<!--BODYCOPY ENDS HERE-->
	</p></td>
	</tr>
